│ patch_type               │ full                                                                                      │
│ patch_name               │ hierarchical_hub_crx                                                                      │
│ patch_description        │ Proposes a more expressive yet parameter-efficient ansatz by introducing per-edge hub     │
│                          │ entanglement via CRX gates. This preserves the data re-uploading structure and            │
│                          │ symmetry-aware pre/post rotations, ring CZ entanglement, and vanila single-qubit gates,   │
│                          │ but adds four separate CRX gates between the center qubit (8) and each edge (1,3,5,7)     │
│                          │ with individual parameters. This increases expressivity while maintaining adjacency       │
│                          │ constraints and the same overall block structure, aiming to improve validation/test       │
│                          │ performance and reduce overfitting by using a modest increase in parameter count          │
│                          │ (N_PARAMS_PER_BLOCK goes from 10 to 13, total N_PARAMS from 60 to 78). Parameter sharing  │
│                          │ is still used for the RZ/RY layers to leverage board symmetry, while hub-edge CRX gates   │
│                          │ receive distinct parameters to capture edge-specific couplings.                           │
