├──────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ patch_type               │ full                                                                                      │
│ patch_name               │ none                                                                                      │
│ patch_description        │ Inspired by the patterns in the prior seeds, this proposal builds a symmetry-aware        │
│                          │ hierarchical ansatz with explicit parameter sharing by board class (corner, edge,         │
│                          │ center). It preserves the fixed data map, uploading structure, and measurement scheme,    │
│                          │ but replaces ANSATZ_SPEC with a more expressive yet compact layout:                       │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ - Layer 1: Pre-entanglement RZ gates grouped by corner/edge/center with shared parameters │
│                          │ across symmetric qubits.                                                                  │
│                          │ - Layer 2: RY rotations likewise grouped by corner/edge/center.                           │
│                          │ - Layer 3: Ring CZ entanglement around the outer cells to propagate correlations.         │
│                          │ - Layer 4: Hub-type entanglement using CRZ gates between the center and each edge, with   │
│                          │ four distinct per-edge parameters to increase expressivity.                               │
│                          │ - Layer 5: Post-entanglement RZ gates grouped by corner/edge/center.                      │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ This design increases expressive capacity (78 parameters per block) while preserving      │
│                          │ symmetry and adjacency constraints, encouraging better generalization and faster          │
│                          │ convergence. It stays within the given gates and connectivity, and reuses the same        │
│                          │ parameter-sharing mechanism as the original framework.                                    │
