│ patch_type               │ full                                                                                      │
│ patch_name               │ none                                                                                      │
│ patch_description        │ We propose a fundamentally different ansatz strategy that preserves the overall           │
│                          │ data-reuploading, 9-qubit Tic-Tac-Toe encoding, and fixed training loop, but changes the  │
│                          │ internal circuit design to be more expressive without increasing parameter count per      │
│                          │ block. Key changes:                                                                       │
│                          │ - Layered, symmetry-aware pre/post rotations: group-based sharing remains (corners,       │
│                          │ edges, center) for both RZ and RY, but the coupling remains structured to leverage board  │
│                          │ symmetry.                                                                                 │
│                          │ - Ring CZ along the outer edge remains to entangle perimeter qubits.                      │
│                          │ - Hub entanglement switched to per-edge CRX between center and each edge (center-edge hub │
│                          │ CRX), enabling a more expressive, parameter-efficient center-to-edge interaction.         │
│                          │ - Added a lightweight inter-edge entanglement stage using fixed CNOT gates along the      │
│                          │ outer ring (0-1, 2-3, 4-5, 6-7) to promote information flow across the ring without       │
│                          │ adding trainable parameters for these gates.                                              │
│                          │ - Post-rotation layer preserved with group sharing to keep parameter count per block at   │
│                          │ 13, keeping total parameters at 78 (N_PARAMS = 13 * N_UPLOADS * N_REPEATS).               │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ This approach introduces a qualitatively different interaction pattern while staying      │
│                          │ within the same constraints (data-uploading, l=3, p=2, adjacency, and parameter sharing). │
│                          │ It should improve validation accuracy and reduce train-test gaps by enabling richer       │
│                          │ entanglement and feature shaping without expanding the parameter budget.                  │
