│ patch_name               │ symmetry_shrunk_param_hub_cry_ring_crx                                                    │
│ patch_description        │ Propose a fundamentally different ansatz design by dramatically reusing parameters across │
│                          │ gates to reduce model complexity and improve generalization. The new ANSATZ_SPEC uses:    │
│                          │ - shared pre/post RZ layers grouped by board symmetry (corner/edge/center)                │
│                          │ - a ring entangler using CRX gates with a single shared parameter around the outer        │
│                          │ perimeter (crx_ring)                                                                      │
│                          │ - hub entanglement using CRY gates from center to each edge, all sharing a single         │
│                          │ parameter (cry_hub_edge)                                                                  │
│                          │ This drastically reduces per-block parameter count (shared across eight ring gates and    │
│                          │ four hub gates), while preserving data-uploading reuploading structure and the fixed      │
│                          │ training loop. The architecture remains within the adjacency constraints and continues to │
│                          │ output per-qubit Z expectations mapped to .                                               │
