│ patch_description        │ Proposes a parameter-efficient ANSATZ_SPEC revision for the 9-qubit tic-tac-toe QML task. │
│                          │ - Ring entanglement uses a single shared CRX parameter around the outer perimeter         │
│                          │ (crx_ring).                                                                               │
│                          │ - Hub entanglement uses two shared parameters across opposite edges: hub_crx for (center, │
│                          │ 1) and (center, 5); hub_cry for (center, 3) and (center, 7). This enforces symmetry and   │
│                          │ reduces parameter count.                                                                  │
│                          │ - All other layers preserve the fixed pre/post RZ and RY symmetry-based sharing, ensuring │
│                          │ compatibility with the training loop.                                                     │
│                          │ - Total parameters per block drop from 13 to 12 (72 total after accounting for 3 uploads  │
│                          │ and 2 repeats), which should improve generalization and stabilize training while          │
│                          │ maintaining expressivity.                                                                 │
│                          │ - Gates remain on allowed adjacent grid edges; the design remains compatible with the     │
│                          │ existing training pipeline (Adam, etc.).                                                  │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ This approach aims to improve validation/test performance and reduce overfitting by       │
│                          │ lowering parameter count and promoting symmetric, bipartisan hub-ring interactions.       │
