│ patch_type               │ cross                                                                                     │
│ patch_name               │ hybrid60_hubcrzcrx                                                                        │
│ patch_description        │ This patch implements a crossover-inspired hybrid ANSATZ_SPEC that merges the strongest   │
│                          │ design choices from the two given seeds while preserving a compact parameter count. The   │
│                          │ key ideas:                                                                                │
│                          │ - Maintain the symmetric pre- and post-entanglement RZ layers and the RY rotations with   │
│                          │ per-group parameter sharing.                                                              │
│                          │ - Keep CZ ring entanglement on the outer perimeter as in both seeds (depth/efficiency     │
│                          │ benefit).                                                                                 │
│                          │ - Introduce hub entanglement between the center qubit (8) and edge qubits (1,3,5,7) using │
│                          │ CRZ and CRX gates, but share a single hub_angle parameter across all hub gates to keep    │
│                          │ N_PARAMS_PER_BLOCK at 10 (thus N_PARAMS = 60 with N_UPLOADS=3 and N_REPEATS=2). This      │
│                          │ preserves parameter efficiency while benefiting from increased expressivity.              │
│                          │ - This design aligns with the best-performing pattern observed (60 params per block) and  │
│                          │ potentially improves validation/test metrics without changing the fixed training loop,    │
│                          │ data construction, measurements, l, p, or feature map.                                    │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ The program preserves all inputs/outputs, only modifying the ANSATZ_SPEC block            │
│                          │ (EVOLVE-BLOCK) to implement the hybrid scheme.                                            │
